Package edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.design

The design package has all the classes necessary to represent XDL designs in RapidSmith.

See:
          Description

Class Summary
Attribute The Attribute object in XDL is used in several places, Design, Instance, Net and Module.
Design The design class houses an entire XDL design or hard macro.
Instance This class represents the inst object in XDL design files.
Module This class represents the modules as found in XDL.
ModuleInstance There is no direct representation of a module instance in XDL.
Net This class represents the nets in XDL.
Pin This class represents the sources and sinks found in net declarations (inpins and outpins)
PIP This class represents the programmable-interconnect-points (PIPs) as found in XDL designs.
Port This class represents the ports used to define the interfaces of modules in XDL.
 

Enum Summary
NetType This enum is simply a way to check net types easier than using Strings.
 

Package edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.design Description

The design package has all the classes necessary to represent XDL designs in RapidSmith. When XDL designs are loaded, the designs populate the classes found within the design package. See Technical Report and Documentation for more information.
